{"id": "22360", "title": "Bug 22360[Fonts] FontRegistry can not instantiated using resources outside org.eclipse.jface.resource", "description": "Bug 22360[Fonts] FontRegistry can not instantiated using resources outside org.eclipse.jface.resource. Therefore, all the resources that are being looked up are the only ones relative to the location of the FontRegistry class org.eclipse.jface.resource path. It can be remedied if FontRegistry took a client class (or class loader) as an additional parameter to the constructor.", "OB": "When I try to create a FontRegistry instance in my application using the code snippet below, I encounter a MissingResourceException:

com.company.product.MyClass

public void createFontRegistry(){
    FontRegistry fonts = new FontRegistry("com.company.product.fonts");
}

I have a file named fonts.properties located in the com/company/product/ folder. However, if I modify the code to use ResourceBundle instead, as shown below, no exception is thrown:

com.company.product.MyClass

public void createFontRegistry(){
    ResourceBundle fonts = ResourceBundle.getBundle("com.company.product.fonts");
}

Additionally, if I create a copy of the FontRegistry class in my com.company.product package, the code works without any issues. Based on my analysis, it seems to be a bug in the FontRegistry class. It attempts to load the fonts resource bundle using the FontRegistry's class loader.", "EB": "The FontRegistry class should allow instantiation using resources located outside the org.eclipse.jface.resource package. It would be helpful if FontRegistry accepted a client class (or class loader) as an additional parameter in the constructor.", "SR": "To reproduce the issue:
1. Create a class in your application, similar to the following:

com.company.product.MyClass

public void createFontRegistry(){
    FontRegistry fonts = new FontRegistry("com.company.product.fonts");
}

2. Ensure that there is a file named fonts.properties located in the com/company/product/ folder.
3. Execute the createFontRegistry() method.

Observe that a MissingResourceException is thrown."}
